"title": "5726: old age, attainment of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5726: old age, attainment of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Attaining old age is regarded as a blessing from God, often as a reward for obedience. The physical weakness brought by old age is recognised; so too is God's ability to strengthen and sustain the aged. Old age is often accompanied by a growth in wisdom and discernment.</p>\n<h2>Life expectancy in the OT</h2>\n<h3>Before the flood</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:5\">GEN 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:8\">GEN 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:11\">GEN 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:27\">GEN 5:27</a> <em>Methuselah died in the year of the flood</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:29\">GEN 9:29</a></p>\n<h3>After the flood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:3\">GEN 6:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:10-Gen11:25\">GEN 11:10–11:25</a> <em>Following the flood, the span of life gradually reduces</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:7-Gen25:8\">GEN 25:7–25:8</a> <em>Abraham's death at 175 is considered “a good old age”.</em></p>\n<h3>In later generations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:10\">PSA 90:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:4-2Sam5:5\">2SA 5:4–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:34-2Sam19:35\">2SA 19:34–19:35</a></p>\n<h2>Attaining old age is a blessing from God</h2>\n<h3>Long life as a reward for obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:33\">DEU 5:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16\">DEU 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:40\">DEU 4:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:1-Prov3:2\">PRO 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:31\">PRO 16:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:13\">ECC 8:13</a></p>\n<h3>Reaching old age is a mark of God's favour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:15\">GEN 15:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:1\">GEN 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:29\">GEN 35:29</a> <em>Isaac</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:32\">JDG 8:32</a> <em>Gideon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:28\">1CH 29:28</a> <em>David, like Abraham and Gideon is described as dying at “a good old age”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:15\">2CH 24:15</a> <em>Jehoiada</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:17\">JOB 42:17</a> <em>Job</em></p>\n<h3>People reaching old age indicates God's blessing on society</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:4\">ZEC 8:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:20\">ISA 65:20</a></p>\n<h3>Seeing grandchildren is a sign of blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:6\">PRO 17:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:11\">GEN 48:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:22-Gen50:23\">GEN 50:22–50:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:15\">RUT 4:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:16\">JOB 42:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps128:5-Ps128:6\">PSA 128:5–128:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10\">ISA 53:10</a></p>\n<h3>Failure to reach old age is a result of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:31-1Sam2:33\">1SA 2:31–2:33</a></p>\n<h2>The disabilities of old age</h2>\n<h3>Its frailties</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:9\">PSA 71:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:1\">GEN 27:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:10\">GEN 48:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:1\">1KI 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:23\">1KI 15:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:2-Eccl12:7\">ECC 12:2–12:7</a> <em>an allegory portraying physical decline</em></p>\n<h3>The progressive inability to have children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:11-Gen18:13\">GEN 18:11–18:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:17\">GEN 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:3\">GEN 37:3</a> <em>Children born in old age were rare and therefore special</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:14\">2KI 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:18\">LUK 1:18</a></p>\n<h3>The approach of death</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:2\">GEN 27:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:15\">1KI 1:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:1\">1CH 23:1</a></p>\n<h2>God's provision for the aged</h2>\n<h3>God strengthens and sustains them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:4\">ISA 46:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:7\">DEU 34:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:10-Josh14:11\">JOS 14:10–14:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:26\">JOB 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:14\">PSA 92:14</a></p>\n<h3>God gives them children</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:7\">GEN 21:7</a> <em>Abraham and Sarah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:16-2Kgs4:17\">2KI 4:16–4:17</a> <em>the Shunammite woman</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:36\">LUK 1:36</a> <em>Elizabeth</em></p>\n<h2>Wisdom and self-control should accompany old age</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:12\">JOB 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:10\">JOB 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:29\">PRO 20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:9\">JHN 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:2\">TIT 2:2</a></p>",
